SUMMARY:🌷🌸 ALLAN GARDENS EASTER TULIP SHOW & LUNCH 🌸🌷
DESCRIPTION:Try New Things in Toronto!\n🌷🌸 ALLAN GARDENS EASTER TULI
 P SHOW & LUNCH 🌸🌷\n\nBlooms\, Warm Conservatory Air & A Classic Dine
 r Finish\nThere’s something magical about stepping into a greenhouse in 
 early spring — especially when the city is still shaking off winter.\nJo
 in us for a relaxed\, social visit to Allan Gardens Conservatory\, where t
 he annual Easter flower show transforms the space into a vibrant escape fi
 lled with colour\, warmth\, and the scent of spring.\nInside the historic 
 glass-domed Palm House (built in 1910!)\, you’ll find a lush collection 
 of tropical plants alongside seasonal displays bursting with tulips\, hydr
 angeas\, Easter lilies\, and blooming bulbs.\n\nThis is not a formal tour.
 \nIt’s a social outing — a chance to wander\, take it all in\, and enj
 oy good company in a beautiful space.\n\n👉 **Don’t forget to join our
  WhatsApp group** – [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi01
 8gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🚶‍♂️ What We’ll Do\nWe’ll
  meet outside and head into Allan Gardens together\, spending about 45 min
 utes to an hour exploring the different greenhouse rooms and seasonal East
 er display.\nThere’s no rush — you’re free to move at your own pace\
 , take photos\, or just soak in the warmth and colour.\nAfterward\, we’l
 l walk over to Fran's Restaurant\, a classic Toronto diner\, for brunch or
  lunch.\nYou’re welcome to join us for a meal or head out after the gard
 ens — totally up to you.\nSometimes the best conversations happen over f
 ries and coffee. 🍳☕\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🌦️ Weather & Expectations\nT
 his event will run rain or shine. The gardens are indoors\, but we will be
  walking outside briefly between locations.\nPlease dress for the weather 
 and wear comfortable shoes.\nAlso — this is NOT a guided or historical t
 our. I’ll share bits of context casually\, but the focus is on social co
 nnection and enjoying the space together.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n🧢 Meetup Detail
 s\n📍 Meetup Location: Meet me in front of Allan Gradens building which 
 is the big white building in the middle of the part\n🫎 I’ll be wearin
 g my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\nI will only wait 5 minutes.\nEa
 rly is on time.\nOn time is late.\nWe’ll head in promptly\, so please pl
 an accordingly and respect everyone’s time.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n🎟️ Meetup
  Fee: $5 cash in person or e-transfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmai
 l.com**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.com%2A%2A/)\nThis helps support the 
 group and allows us to keep hosting events like this. Thank you for suppor
 ting community! 💖\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🎒 What to Bring\nWater\nComfortabl
 e walking shoes\nA small snack (optional)\nCamera or phone for photos 🌷
 \nWeather-appropriate clothing\nPlease also use the washroom before arrivi
 ng\, as stops are limited.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\nThis gro
 up is open to anyone who wants to be social and make friends — whether s
 ingle or not.\n\nWe also host:\n🎬 Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts
  & culture outings\n🍽️ Restaurant gatherings\nThere’s always someth
 ing happening.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\nREMEMBER: You’re welcome to just show up 
 on the day if you’re unsure about your schedule.\nAnd as always\, someti
 mes plans shift and events may need to be canceled — please keep an eye 
 on updates.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathew\nQuestions? Post on the
  event wall or email\n\n📧 [torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com](mailto:
 torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com)\nCome for the flowers. Stay for the w
 armth.\nLeave feeling like you stepped into spring — even if it’s stil
 l winter outside. 🌸✨
